The paper focuses on using deep learning for image classification to block ads, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses privacy concerns related to online advertising, which could fall under the cybersecurity (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of deep learning for image classification also falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance overhead of implementing deep neural networks, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the ad blocker within the browser's image rendering pipeline, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
